parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Erratic Engine Behavior and ECU Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Control Unit (ECU) can cause erratic engine behavior, complete engine failure, and stalling, leading to safety risks, especially when driving with passengers, and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine revving up to high RPMs in neutral

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic idle and engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: engine dying or stalling for no reason

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ECU Failure Causing Erratic Idle and Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU can cause the vehicle to stall or experience erratic idle, leading to a significant safety risk to the driver and others, especially when stopping in busy intersections.
symptoms: idle dropping with the car often stalling
stalling when the clutch is depressed for a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the check engine light or transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belts can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The rear seat belts will not retract from their position
the rear seat belts are stuck
the rear seat belts need replacement.
